From: SerenityOS Developers <serenityos@serenityos.org>
Date: Mon, 1 Jan 2024 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] base: Add SerenityOS platform implementation

Add platform-serenity.cc with SerenityOS-specific implementations of
OS:: methods, and wire it up in BUILD.gn. Modeled after platform-freebsd.cc.

JIT is not supported in this initial port (built with v8_jitless=true),
so no code-mapping allocator is needed.
---
 src/base/platform/BUILD.gn              |   4 +
 src/base/platform/platform-serenity.cc | 102 +++++++++++++++++++++++++
 2 files changed, 106 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 src/base/platform/platform-serenity.cc

diff --git a/src/base/platform/BUILD.gn b/src/base/platform/BUILD.gn
index 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000..aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa 100644
--- a/src/base/platform/BUILD.gn
+++ b/src/base/platform/BUILD.gn
@@ -50,6 +50,10 @@ v8_source_set("base-platform") {
       "platform-haiku.cc",
     ]
   }
+  if (is_serenity) {
+    sources += [
+      "platform-serenity.cc",
+    ]
+  }
   if (is_linux || is_android) {
     sources += [
       "platform-linux.cc",
